Serves 2 with leftovers
There are 3 parts to this: prawns, noodles, stirfry
/////
Prawns:
    Place the following in a bowl:
          Somewhere between 10-20 prawns
          About a tablespoon finely diced or minced ginger
          About 5* cloves of garlic
          A sliced red chilli
          A couple tablespoons kecap Manis
          A tablespoon sesame oil
    Leave to marinate while you make the noodles
/////
Noodles:
    Cook according to instructions (usually 7 minutes):
          200g (or similar) dried fat rice noodles
    Drain and rinse with lots of cold water
    Mix together:
          A tablespoon brown sugar
          2 tablespoons dark soy sauce
    In a bowl pour the sugar/soy over the noodles and mix to coat
    Heat a fry pan and oil lightly
    Add the noodles and fry for about 5 minutes, stirring a couple of times, aiming for some charr / crisp in places
    Set noodles aside
/////
Stirfry preparation:
    Prepare the following in a little bowl:
          1* sliced red chilli
          4* tablespoons black chinese vinegar (e.g. Heng Shun Chinkiang)
    Set aside (this is the dressing at the end)
    Prepare the following:
          Florettes of 1* head broccoli
          Rough chopped bok choy
          Sliced spring onion
          Snow peas / sugar snap peas / any other greens
/////
Stirfry:
    Heat clean pan till hot
    Add prawns and marinade, cook each side for a bit so the prawns get some colour
    Add greens and stirfry till barely cooked
      Optional, if you have a big enough pan and can find a clear corner, add:
          2* beaten eggs
      Cook till it's like a loose scramble then mix in with the veg  
    Add noodles and stir through
Serve with the vinegar and chilli dressing
